            <q>the completion of any other investigation relating to any of the matters".</q>
            The noble Lord went on to say that a decision that was not taken with sufficient care or on sufficient grounds could be subject to judicial review. If he is looking at the matter again, the decision would need to be on a matter of significance otherwise that is a complete let-out. When one sees the word "any" in a Bill, one starts to wonder just how wide that provision is&#x2014;and this could not be much wider.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0668P0-02932'>
        <a name='S5LV0668P0_20050119_GCR_45'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-william-goodhart' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
